Name: Description
Parental Employment Instability: The share of children living in households where neither the householder nor a spouse worked full-time in the last year.

Name: Source Notes
Parental Employment Instability: U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey 1-Year Estimates, Public Use Microdata Sample File (2005 - 2019, 2021-2022).

Name: Notes
Parental Employment Instability: Please note, we do not report 2020 American Community Survey 1-year estimates. Due to disruptions and biases in data collection during 2020, the Census Bureau released the “experimental” 1-year estimates for 2020 and advises against comparing against estimates from prior or future years.
